The paper deals with the security and privacy issues in spectrum sharing in wireless communication networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves the use of blockchain technology, which can also be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves simulation and performance analysis, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG).
